76561198217041065,Recommended,434000,32158621,Posted: 3 June,all,HipsterGoat,"This game is beautiful and wonderful. Just from the beginning, you can tell that Might and Delight put lots of work into the designs and patterns in the forest. I say that this game is adorable and takes you on a little lynx's journey throughout her first steps.Get ready for a rollarcoaster:SPOILERS: TURN BACK NOW IF YOU WANT TO!You start out as a little lynx, snuggled up with her siblings at her mother's lap. Then, the mother takes them out for the first time. You get to play games, tackle your brothers and sisters, and eat your first prey. Then, your mother takes you to the river, where you play and run. Then, it overflows. Squealing at the top of your lungs, you are carried across the river by your mother. But then, another kitten squeaks for help. The mother trips and loses you. You yowl for help, and the mother turns around and sees you being carried away. She yowls back, racing desprately to reach you. But a huge wave crashes on top of both you and your mother, and you are carried away as your mother continues to yowl and run after you.You wash up on a creek bed. You open your eyes and explore. Mean swans thrust you about and you get scared from all the big birds. You are trampled from a deer herd, and you try hard to sniff out the trail to your mother. You sniff, following the scent. Sometimes you can see the outlines of you mother, her and your littermates calling your name. They are searching for you, like you are for them. Soon, weary and tired, you come to a clearing in the forest. There, sleeping in the middle, is a lost, little bear cub.You hunt for the bear. The bear cub eats three finches before it walks around with you. Maybe he could help you find your mother...This game is adorable, I've said that already but I can't say it enough. It's heartbreakingly lovingly. If you want to see a fan-fiction version of this, go to my screenshots and start from the beginning. This game is fun, but there are TWO IMPORTANT THINGS that YOU and MIGHT AND DELIGHT need to know:1. This game is super quick. I finished it in three hours. Not worth $15, despite the amazing graphics and attention put into it. More like $10. But I still 100% recommend it.2. To make the lynx look up, you have to right click, hold it, and scroll DOWN. I mean, I got used to it, but it still threw me off. Maybe you could fix this?So, to come to a conculsion, this game is fun, safe, singleplayer, and has beautiful graphics and designs."
