,Not Recommended,434000,26251493,"Posted: 27 October, 2016",all,irlgarbodor,"This game is beautiful, sweet and absolutely adorable! But there were too many drawbacks keeping me from actually enjoying it.This game might be more aptly titled ""Lost in the Woods Simulator 2016"". The dizzying watercolors of the environment mixed with similar-themed areas make it very difficult to find your way. There is a 'sense' mode where you can sniff to try and find your mother, and sometimes her paw prints will appear in a trail, showing you the way. My issue with this was that 1) these hints didn't appear often enough for me and 2) when they did appear, it was extremely difficult to tell which way they were leading. I spent way too much time just walking around in circles, trying to find my way.The controls are not explained very well, not even if you explicitly go into the keybindings menu. When I found the baby bear and it was clear he was hungry and I had to feed him in order to wake him up, I had SUCH a difficult time figuring out how to pick up food and bring it to him without eating it myself.If it wasn't for the confusion completely jarring me out of the experience, both through the environment and the keybindings (I was playing with an Xbox controller btw), it would be a really cute game. I feel that either the implementation of a minimap or a clear idea of which direction's the mother lynx's paw prints are going would at the very least make this a less painful game to play."
