,Recommended,434000,34183231,Posted: 11 August,all,Momolove,"I had loved the first and second games, and I also decided to get this game. From the trailers, I decided it was a game where you played as a lynx cub, stayed with your family, escaped danger, and grow up and leave your mother. Then you would survive on your own, find a mate, and leave them to raise your family. Then you would have to play Shelter 2. I was so wrong. Below is the story, which I recommend not reading for the game is best going in blind.In Paws you play as a lynx cub, with you lynx family. Any new player would immediatly get attached with their family, for you play around with your siblings and follow your mother. After sleeping on the second day, you wake up near dawn to see your mother walking away from the den. You follow your mother  up a hill and see a star. After looking at the star for a while, it floats into the sky. Then you and your mother go to sleep.When you wake up its all cloudy. You follow your mother out of the den, over a log, and then the story progresses. Then its raining. You and your siblings are most likely either scared, tired, or hungry, for when you meow, you sound more depressed.Then you come across a river. Your mother picks you up and walks across it, your siblings swimming along. Then a wave washes you out of your mother's grasp. You get stunned in the water for a second when you start to swim along. Your mother picks up one of your siblings and the other two make it onto shore. But then another wave comes. Your mother puts the other cub on the shore and runs after you. The wave then washes you away before your mother can grab you.You then wake up and proceed to search for your family. After traveling, following your family's footprints, and resting, you wake up due to a pack of hunting wolves. You run along, and meet a bear cub. After feeding it three birds or berries, it will become strong again and follow you around, helping you.At some point of your search, you'll come to a foggy area. If you sniff around, you can find a hidden 'ghost' of your family.  But a fox is also among the ghost, and in it the fox seems to be hunting your other three siblings. Then you go through a tunnel and need to find a way for your bear friend to follow you. You then will enter a foggy bit, and music will start playing. There are platforms that you can jump onto, which is important to do because the fox will attempt to attack you.If you get attacked, then the screen will go black and you can hear the fox biting into the cub when the bear suddenly attacks it and chases the fox off. You will then wake up in a den that the bear brought you two. It will leave and come back with a fish. The bear then drops the fish and covers the den with branches to camoflauge it.When you wake up you will walk along as normal but then your friend will run off. If you follow the bear, then you will come across a river.Across the river is your mother and two of your siblings. Here you have the choice. Swim across the river to your family or stay with your bear friend. If you go with your mother, then everytime you try to go back your mother will pick you up. If you go with your bear friend, your friend will eat one berry bushes and you go through them to go to a den. It also is possible to go with your mother and when she goes to sleep with your siblings, you can go across the river to your bear and go with the bear ending, but only if you had your friend eat the bushes first.At the ending, you climb up a hill and see a star come down. You will see who you left behind, which I found heartbreaking.Strangly, the other Shelter games didn't make me cry when a cub died or when I got to the ending. But when I got to the ending of Paws for the first time, I cried. Even when I see the ending now, I still feel sad. Its pretty rare for a game to make me cry, and even more rare for me to feel the same feeling at the same part over and over again."
