76561197971739421,Recommended,434000,29536902,Posted: 28 January,all,Zergling Rush Of Adorableness!,"Yet another beautiful game in the Shelter series and like the others, Paws is both simplistic and emotional. It dishes out a delightful story that sticks true to nature and really puts you in the 'paws' of your lynx cub character.The game is perfectly made in every way. I mean, cute little mewling sounds are just so darn adorable. But there are a couple of cons to this that in no way made me think bad or even get annoyed at it. Just slight inconveniences really.The controls are a tad oversensitive when controlling the camera. This can take a little time getting used to but every game has its unique feel and Paws certainly gives you plenty of breathing room to master the controls.If you, like me, love going for achievements too, just be aware the game will only reward you the ones you've earned once you've shut down the game. This makes it hard, especially for the puff ball achievement, to keep track of how many you've knocked off.I found this game to have no real challenge, just simple fun. The previous Shelter games did have more challenges to them. This doesn't change my love for this game, however I do wish there were points in it that enacted serious danger to both characters to put across how deadly the real world is to young cubs alone in the wild.Overall a delightful game, beautiful storyline, and certainly pulls on the emotional strings to your heart. I highly recommend this game if you love playing as animals. You don't have to worry about playing the other Shelter games as they all have separate stories. This game is very short but the enjoyment goes on forever. Give it a try!Also, beware the swans. Those buggers are nasty! ;)"
